      "anchor": "#13-conflict-of-interest",
      "title": "13. CONFLICT OF INTEREST",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "All members of the Urethral Strictures guidelines working group have provided disclosure statements of all relationships that they have that might be perceived as a potential source of a conflict of interest. This information is provided below and is also publicly available on the EAU website: https://uroweb.org/guidelines/urethral-strictures/panel . This guidelines document was developed with the financial support of the European Association of Urology. No external sources of funding and support have been involved. The EAU is a non-profit organisation, and funding is limited to administrative and travel and meeting expenses. No honoraria or other reimbursements have been provided. Disclosures: The EAU Guidelines Office certifies that all conflicts of interest, including specific financial interests and relationships and affiliations relevant to the subject matter or materials discussed in the manuscript (eg, employment/ affiliation, grants or funding, consultancies, honoraria, stock ownership or options, expert testimony, royalties, or patents filed, received, or pending), are the following: N. Lumen reported receiving grants or research support from Janssen Pharmaceutica. F. Campos Juanatey reported receiving travel grants from Casen Recordati; receiving company speaker honoraria or consultant fees from Boston Scientific, Laboratorios Rubió, S.a. and Laborie Medical Measurement Systems B.V. T.J. Greenwell reported receiving company speaker honoraria from Boston Scientific. N.I. Osman reported financial interest from Urotronic. M. Waterloos reported receiving company honoraria or consultant fees from Coloplast and EAU research foundation. M. Oszczudlowski reported receiving company consultation fees from Medtronic Poland Sp. Z O.o. K. Dimitropoulos, F. Martins, A. Ploumidis, S. Riechardt, R. Barratt, G, Chan, W. Verla and F. Esperto have nothing to declare.",
